“Procrastination kills talent” - @malikhooker24 

We had a great conversation with Malik Hooker of the Dallas Cowboys last night on IG Live. The question to him was that if he was able to sit down with his younger self what are some words he would share with himself.

Procrastination kills talent and keep the faith was perfect because often times in life many of us never are able to reach our full potential due to procrastination and the lack of faith we have in ourselves or our capabilities. So if you’re out there reading and watching stay hungry despite the obstacles in your way and trust in God throughout the storms.

You can check out the full interview on our page!
